ENTRY       EC 1.3.98.2                 Enzyme
NAME        fumarate reductase (CoM/CoB);
            thiol:fumarate reductase;
            Tfr
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-CH group of donors;
            With other, known, acceptors
SYSNAME     fumarate CoM:CoB oxidoreductase (succinate forming)
REACTION    fumarate + CoM + CoB = succinate + CoM-S-S-CoB [RN:R10660]
ALL_REAC    R10660
SUBSTRATE   fumarate [CPD:C00122];
            CoM [CPD:C03576];
            CoB
PRODUCT     succinate [CPD:C00042];
            CoM-S-S-CoB [CPD:C04832]
COMMENT     The enzyme, isolated from the archaeon Methanobacterium thermoautotrophicum, is very oxygen sensitive. It cannot use reduced flavins, reduced coenzyme F420, or NAD(P)H as an electron donor. Distinct from EC 1.3.1.6 [fumarate reductase (NADH)], EC 1.3.5.1 [succinate dehydrogenase (ubiquinone)], and EC 1.3.5.4 [fumarate reductase (quinol)].
